        <abstract>
            <p>Rabbits’ coats true in character. If the next ones are true, it is superfluous to keep trying.</p>
            <p>Does not know why crying children rub eyes with knuckles.</p> 
<p>Mentions FG’s article on prayer ["Statistical inquiries into the efficacy of prayer", <hi rend="italic">Fortn. Rev.</hi> n.s. 12 (1872): 125–35].</p> 
